1 unit(s) Lentils, canned
4 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 unit(s) Lime
3 tbsp Guacamole
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
2 unit(s) Green Onion
285 g Shrimp
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Thinly slice green onions.
Halve tomatoes.
Zest, then juice lime into a medium bowl.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp, then pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse lentils.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then lentils and garlic puree. Cook, stirring often, until lentils are warmed through and garlic is fragrant, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Add shrimp. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp just turn pink, 2-3 min.**
Add chipotle sauce and half the onions. Cook, stirring often, until warmed through, 1-2 min.
Remove from heat.

Wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave until tortillas are warm and flexible, 1 min.
Divide shrimp-lentil filling between tortillas, then sprinkle over feta. Roll filled tortillas tightly.
Place filled tortillas, seam-side down, on a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Brush with 2 tsp oil.

Bake taquitos in the middle of the oven until light brown, 7-8 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 parchment-lined baking sheets and bake in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Add tomatoes, remaining green onions and 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil to the medium bowl with lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. Set aside
In a small bowl, add lime zest, sour cream and guacamole, then stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper, then set aside.

Divide taquitos between plates.
Dollop over avocado crema and salsa.

If you've opted to add shrimp, using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp, then pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper. Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then lentils and garlic puree. Cook, stirring often, until lentils are warmed through and garlic is fragrant, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper. Add shrimp. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp just turn pink, 2-3 min.**  Add chipotle sauce and half the onions. Cook, stirring often, until warmed through, 1-2 min. Fill tortillas as indicated in the recipe.

Répartir la garniture de crevettes dans les tortillas.